In a world chasing modern minimalism, Iftekhar chose nostalgia.
Brick by brick, memory by memory, The Calcutta Bungalow was born.

In this reel from Host Diaries EP01, Iftekhar takes us through the soulful origin story of this century-old home turned boutique heritage stay. Each room tells a tale inspired by old professions, forgotten trades, and the spirit of a Kolkata that refuses to be erased.

Here’s what this segment reveals:

Why he didn’t just renovate, but resurrect a crumbling North Kolkata building
The stories behind rooms named after typists, dhobis, and kabuliwalas
How design became a medium of cultural storytelling
The emotional weight of restoring a place with history in its walls
A vision to make Calcutta not just a destination, but a feeling

This isn’t just architecture.
It’s memory, preserved.

Catch the full episode here:
📺 YouTube: Host Diaries

latestPosts.caption:
She never really said it out loud,
but somewhere in her heart,
she hoped for a quiet picture—
in a simple saree,
with a tiny bindi
and the soft clink of bangles.

Just a moment frozen in time…
Just to remember what it feels like—
to look like home,
to feel like herself
in the most timeless way.

Maybe on a slow afternoon in Kolkata,
where tram bells ring and old houses lean into the breeze,
as if the city, too, remembers.

A camera’s gentle shutter—
capturing her not just as she is,
but as someone who belongs
to a story that began long before her,
and still quietly continues.…. #kolkataphotography #cityofjoykolkata #ｃｉｔｙｏｆｊｏｙ #nostalgia #bengal #bengalbeauty

Not just a meal — this is a memory on a plate. 🍽️ 

Our Calcutta Bungalow Special Thali brings together the essence of a Bengali home.
Slow-cooked curries, crispy fries, heirloom recipes, and festive favourites, all served on terracotta ware with love.

Every bite carries a story of grandmothers, street markets, and Sunday lunches.
Rooted in tradition, crafted with care, and best enjoyed slowly.

Come hungry. Leave nostalgic.✨ 

Available in both Veg & Non Veg options!
